        "57035": {
          "vnum": 57035,
          "name": "Rotting Woods",
          "description": "The forest floor is littered here with the rotting corpses of fallen trees and dying brush. New growth sprouts from the old, thriving in the noxious, humid air. From the west, the silence of the dark forest is broken by the howling of a wolf, perhaps as it prepares to feast on the flesh of some less fortunate denizen of the forest, or, more likely, some less fortunate visitor. The forest is open in all directions, and the river lies to the south.",
